<h2>Semantic HTML Structure</h2>

<section>
  <h3>V2 Markup Philosophy</h3>
  <p>The V2 templates use semantic HTML5 elements with zero classes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>&lt;header&gt;</code> - Site header with logo and navigation</li>
    <li><code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> - Navigation menus and card grids</li>
    <li><code>&lt;main&gt;</code> - Main content area</li>
    <li><code>&lt;section&gt;</code> - Content sections and FAQ categories</li>
    <li><code>&lt;article&gt;</code> - FAQ answers and standalone content</li>
    <li><code>&lt;aside&gt;</code> - Disclaimers and warnings</li>
    <li><code>&lt;footer&gt;</code> - Site footer</li>
    <li><code>&lt;details&gt;</code> + <code>&lt;summary&gt;</code> - Accordions</li>
    <li><code>&lt;data&gt;</code> - Badges with semantic values</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<h2>CSS Architecture</h2>

<section>
  <h3>Semantic Selectors</h3>
  <p>All styles use element selectors, pseudo-classes, and combinators:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>body > header</code> - Direct child selector for page header</li>
    <li><code>main > section</code> - FAQ category sections</li>
    <li><code>main > nav > a</code> - Navigation cards</li>
    <li><code>details[open]</code> - Attribute selector for open accordions</li>
    <li><code>summary::before</code> - Pseudo-element for accordion arrow</li>
    <li><code>a:hover</code> - Hover states throughout</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Zero classes</strong> - All styling is based on document structure and semantic meaning.</p>
</section>

